  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the element in the list containing the allowed elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArgumentConstraint<T>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.Set<T>

    public class AllowedSetConstraint<T>
extends java.util.HashSet<T>
implements ArgumentConstraint<T>
    This constraint is used to specify a list of allowed elements, from which the given argument have to be later selected.
